	"description": "Webpack [https://webpack.js.org/] is a powerful bundler and dependency manager\nused by many enterprise-level companies as tooling for their front-end code.\n\nTypically, webpack is configured when a project is first set up, and small\ntweaks are then made to the config files as needed from time to time. Because of\nthis, many developers don’t have a lot of experience working with webpack.\n\nIn this hands-on tutorial, we’ll go through the basics of setting up your very\nown production-ready webpack con",
